'''''Rauhan Puolesta''''' (''Pro Peace'' in English)<ref name=ra/> is a [[Finnish language]] [[news magazine]] published in [[Finland]].

==History and profile==
Rauhan Puolesta, a cultural and news magazine, is published by the Finnish Peace Committee.<ref name=ra>{{cite web|title=Association|url=http://www.rauhanpuolustajat.org/english/|work=Rauhanpuolustajat|accessdate=26 January 2014}}</ref> It appears six times a year and disseminates the news about the committee.<ref>{{cite web|title=Informal Learning and Civic Diplomacy around the Breakfast Table|url=https://tampub.uta.fi/bitstream/handle/10024/68233/a_flying_finn_2013.pdf?sequence=1|work=Tampere Peace Research Institute|accessdate=26 January 2014|author=Karim Maiche|location=Tampere|format=TAPRI Net Series. No:5|date=2013}}</ref> The magazine has both in print and online versions.<ref>{{cite web|title=Finnish Peace Committee <U+2013> a short description|url=http://laplandpeace.wordpress.com/tag/finnish-peace-committee-international-peace-movement/|work=Lapland Peace Committee|accessdate=26 January 2014}}</ref>

